President Biden called the Mayors of Fort Myers, Cape Coral, Sarasota, and the Chair of Charlotte County in Florida to assure them that the Federal government is fully supporting their communities as Hurricane Ian hits Florida. He spoke with Mayor Kevin Anderson of Fort Myers and discussed the ongoing needs of the city, including support for vulnerable groups such as the elderly, families living in mobile homes, and other community members affected by the storm. Messages were left for the Mayors of Cape Coral and Sarasota, as well as the Chair of Charlotte County.